The paper proposes a new one-class classifier that uses parallel hyperplanes to improve the performance of the one-class SVM. This work involves machine learning and pattern recognition, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the proposed method is evaluated on image datasets, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of kernel methods to learn non-linear decision functions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the experiments involve evaluating the performance of the proposed method, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.DM (Data Mining).
